0won't%20be%20fully%20approved%20by%20regulators%20until%20late%202025%2C%20Gregory%20Koumoullos%2C%20ConEd's%20department%20manager%20of%20thermal%20energy%20networks%2C%20said.%20But%20the%20intention%20is%20to%20eventually%20scale%20the%20networks%20to%20help%20New%20York%20achieve%20its%20climate%20goals%2C%20because%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20buildings%20accounts%20for%2032%25%20of%20the%20state's%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20single%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pilot%20could%20be%20one%20of%20three%20that%20ConEd%20builds%20in%20and%20around%20New%20York%20City%20to%20test%20a%20cleaner%20way%20of%20delivering%20energy%20to%20customers.%20The%20proposals%20are%20in%20the%20design%20phase%20and%20likely%20won't%20be%20fully%20approved%20by%20regulators%20until%20late%202025%2C%20Gregory%20Koumoullos%2C%20ConEd's%20department%20manager%20of%20thermal%20energy%20networks%2C%20said.%20But%20the%20intention%20is%20to%20scale%20up%20the%20networks%20to%20help%20New%20York%20achieve%20its%20climate%20goals%2C%20because%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20buildings%20accounts%20for%2032%25%20of%20the%20state's%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20single%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20pilots%20go%20well%2C%20they%20could%20prove%20a%20business%20model%20for%20other%20gas%20utilities%20to%20follow%20to%20decarbonize%20entire%20neighborhoods%2C%20and%20potentially%20lower%20energy%20bills%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20pilots%20are%20just%20the%20first%20phase%2C%26quot%3B%20Koumoullos%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20larger%20the%20network%20you%20have%2C%20the%20lower%20the%20cost%20is%20because%20you%20can%20connect%20more%20customers%20with%20less%20infrastructure%20and%20they%20are%20sharing%20more%20waste%20heat.%20Thermal%20networks%20really%20bloom%20at%20a%20larger%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20isn't%20new.%20But%20ConEd%20is%20among%20the%20first%20utilities%20in%20the%20country%20to%20propose%20thermal%20energy%20networks%20after%20New%20York%20enacted%20a%20law%20two%20years%20ago%20requiring%20the%20utility%20to%20try%20it.%20Six%20other%20states%2C%20including%20Colorado%20and%20Massachusetts%2C%20have%20enacted%20similar%20laws%20either%20allowing%20or%20mandating%20pilots.%20Gas%20utilities%20have%20legal%20mandates%20to%20sell%20gas%2C%20so%20states%20have%20to%20pass%20laws%20allowing%20them%20to%20expand%20into%20new%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Framingham%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20the%20utility%20Eversource%20is%20leading%20the%20way.%20The%20utility%20already%20connected%20dozens%20of%20residential%20and%20commercial%20buildings%20to%20a%20geothermal%20network%20for%20a%20two-year%20pilot%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbur.org%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2F08%2Fnetworked-geothermal-eversource-framingham-pilot-project-decarbonization%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWBUR%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20project%20involved%20drilling%20boreholes%20hundreds%20of%20feet%20below%20ground%2C%20where%20the%20temperature%20is%20usually%20a%20constant%2055%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%20Water%20pipes%20are%20connected%20to%20ground-source%20electric%20heat%20pumps%20in%20buildings%2C%20which%20exchange%20and%20push%20energy%20around%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConEd%20is%20proposing%20its%20own%20geothermal%20network%20for%20Mount%20Vernon%2C%20a%20suburban%20neighborhood%20north%20of%20New%20York%20City%20where%20up%20to%2076%20buildings%2C%20including%20homes%2C%20apartment%20complexes%2C%20churches%2C%20and%20fire%20stations%2C%20could%20be%20hooked%20up.%20But%20drilling%20boreholes%20isn't%20always%20feasible%20in%20densely%20packed%20cities%2C%20which%20is%20why%20capturing%20waste%20heat%20from%20data%20centers%20and%20other%20buildings%20is%20being%20tested.%20Rockefeller%20Center%20in%20NYC%20is%20the%20other%20proposed%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f12dc53-e013-48cb-ae17-f381e823311d%5C%22%3EHigh%20upfront%20costs%2C%20but%20long-term%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetrofitting%20buildings%20and%20laying%20new%20pipes%20is%20expensive.%20The%20estimated%20price%20tag%20of%20all%20three%20pilots%20combined%20is%20%24255%20million%2C%20which%20would%20be%20spread%20across%20ConEd's%20customer%20base%2C%20Koumoullos%20said.%20For%20those%20participating%20in%20the%20pilots%2C%20ConEd%20would%20guarantee%20that%20energy%20costs%20won't%20go%20up%20during%20a%205-year%20test%20period.%20The%20utility%20is%20also%20looking%20at%20tax%20breaks%20under%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20to%20offset%20the%20cost%20to%20customers.%20ConEd%20would%20use%20the%20pilots%20to%20find%20out%20the%20actual%20costs%20of%20building%20thermal%20energy%20systems%20and%20test%20different%20ways%20to%20charge%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20up-front%20costs%20are%20a%20barrier%20to%20wider%20adoption.%20But%20climate%20advocates%20point%20out%20that%20an%20increasing%20amount%20of%20money%20is%20also%20being%20spent%20on%20replacing%20old%20gas%20lines%20every%20year.%20Between%202011%20and%202022%2C%20gas%20utilities'%20capital%20expenditures%20on%20distribution%20infrastructure%20tripled%20from%20%247%20billion%20a%20year%20to%20nearly%20%2421%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20HEET%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets-global.website-files.com%2F649aeb5aaa8188e00cea66bb%2F663a27270c0fa4fffcfe447d_Leaked-and-Combusted-May-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20climate-solutions%20nonprofit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20spearheaded%20the%20push%20for%20thermal%20energy%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20utility-scale%20projects%20can%20recoup%20the%20upfront%20costs%20in%20energy%20savings%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20That%20was%20the%20case%20at%20Colorado%20Mesa%20University%2C%20which%20built%20a%20geothermal%20network%20in%202008.%20Kent%20Marsh%2C%20the%20university's%20vice%20president%20for%20capital%20planning%20sustainability%20and%20campus%20operations%2C%20said%20switching%20to%20geothermal%20saved%20%241.5%20million%20a%20year.%20The%20system%20paid%20for%20itself%20within%20about%2011%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Hood%2C%20the%20manager%20of%20new%20product%20development%20at%20Vermont%20Gas%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20some%20utilities%20are%20looking%20for%20new%20business%20models.%20Vermont%20Gas%20aims%20to%20be%20net%20zero%20by%202050%2C%20so%20is%20considering%20community%20geothermal%20as%20a%20way%20to%20get%20there.%20Hood%20helped%20launch%20the%20Utility%20Networked%20Geothermal%20Collaborative%2C%20which%20now%20includes%2027%20gas%20utilities%20in%20North%20America%20that%20serve%20about%20half%20the%20customers%20in%20the%20US%2C%20so%20they%20can%20keep%20tabs%20on%20pilot%20projects%20and%20share%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20eyes%20are%20on%20New%20York%2C%20in%20large%20part%20because%20it%20will%20show%20how%20these%20systems%20can%20be%20regulated%20within%20a%20utility%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-thermal-energy-con-edison-sustainability-pollution-2024-08%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723113868000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dee819179d7574527631f65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-thermal-energy-con-edison-sustainability-pollution-2024-08%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20utility%20Con%20Edison%20plans%20to%20test%20climate-friendly%20thermal%20energy%20networks%20at%20data%20centers%20and%20other%20buildings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-thermal-energy-con-edison-sustainability-pollution-2024-08%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%