h%20forward%20to%20today%2C%20and%20the%20prices%20for%20those%20same%20goods%20have%20shot%20up%20to%20%242.71%2C%20%245.47%2C%20and%20%24412%2C000.%20Prices%20are%20up%20about%2045%25%20across%20the%20board.%20But%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20has%20stayed%20constant%3F%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcurrent-federal-minimum-wage-is-13-years-old-inflation-impact-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20minimum%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20stuck%20at%20%247.25%20an%20hour%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20see%20the%20issue%3A%20People%20making%20the%20mandated%20minimum%20have%20far%20less%20purchasing%20power%20than%20they%20once%20did.%20The%20silver%20lining%20is%20that%20thanks%20to%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20very%20few%20workers%20actually%20make%20%247.25.%20According%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20of%20the%20nearly%2080%20million%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20who%20are%20paid%20hourly%20rates%2C%20only%201.3%25%2C%20or%20about%201%20million%2C%20are%20paid%20at%20or%20below%20that%20federal%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20situation%2C%20here's%20an%20idea%3A%20Why%20not%20raise%20the%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20right%20now%3F%20It%20wouldn't%20be%20a%20big%20deal%20for%20businesses%2C%20which%20by%20and%20large%20aren't%20paying%20%247.25%20anyway%2C%20and%20it%20would%20lock%20in%20gains%20that%20low-wage%20workers%20have%20made%20in%20recent%20years%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20downturn.%20Thanks%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw25434%2Fw25434.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espillover%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20increase%20may%20have%2C%20it%20could%20also%20help%20workers%20beyond%20those%20making%20the%20lowest%20wages%20and%20bump%20up%20their%20pay%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20a%20higher%20minimum%20wage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwpcarey.asu.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2FMinimum%2520Wage%2520and%2520Individual%2520Worker%2520Productivity.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20increase%20worker%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lower%20turnover%20costs%20for%20businesses%20because%20workers%20stick%20with%20their%20employers%20longer.%20It%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fpublication%2Fa-15-minimum-wage-would-have-significant-and-direct-effects-on-the-federal-budget%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520estimated%2520annual%2520reductions%2520due%2C2025%2520and%2520later%2520years%2520than%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20government%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20public%20assistance%20programs%20and%20put%20more%20money%20into%20consumers'%20pockets%20for%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fideas.repec.org%2Fa%2Ffip%2Ffedhle%2Fy2013iaugn313.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20aggregate%20household%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20boost%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20seems%20like%20a%20win-win-win%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20workers%2C%20and%20even%20businesses%20(though%20many%20won't%20say%20that)%2C%20Congress%20has%20resisted%20raising%20the%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20for%20the%20past%20decade%20and%20a%20half.%20Getting%20anything%20done%20legislatively%20is%20always%20a%20challenge%2C%20especially%20in%20an%20election%20year%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dataforprogress.org%2Fblog%2F2023%2F5%2F24%2F725-isnt-cutting-it-in-this-economy-voters-support-raising-the-minimum-wage-to-20-per-hour%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolls%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2021%2F04%2F22%2Fmost-americans-support-a-15-federal-minimum-wage%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindicate%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20higher%20minimum%20wage%20is%20broadly%20popular.%20Many%20states%2C%20red%20and%20blue%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-raise-minimum-wage-increase-january-2024-state-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20implemented%20higher%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20have%20even%20done%20so%20by%20voter%20referendum%2C%20including%20Nebraska%20and%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20not%20exactly%20Democratic%20strongholds.%20Even%20if%20it's%20not%20on%20the%202024%20agenda%2C%20it%20could%20be%20on%20the%20radar%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20for%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20think%20that%20this%20would%20be%20an%20uncontroversial%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20just%20pass%20a%20minimum%20wage%2C%20give%20these%20workers%20a%20higher%20wage%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yannet%20Lathrop%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20and%20policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20National%20Employment%20Law%20Program.%20%26quot%3BBut%20nothing%20is%20easy%2C%20obviously%2C%20in%20Washington.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20in%20uncharted%20territory%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20federal%20minimum-wage%20hikes.%20This%20is%20the%20longest%20period%20that%20the%20national%20floor%20hasn't%20increased%20since%20it%20was%20implemented%20in%201938.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%247.25%20minimum%20is%20also%20out%20of%20step%20with%20the%20many%20states%20and%20municipalities%20that%20have%20wage%20standards%20separate%20from%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20above%20%E2%80%94%20the%20federal%20number.%20Arizona's%20minimum%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20%2414.35%2C%20California's%20%2416%2C%20Florida's%20%2412%2C%20and%20West%20Virginia's%20%248.75.%20Seattle's%20minimum%20wage%20for%20large%20businesses%20is%20%2419.97%2C%20and%20for%20smaller%20ones%20it's%20%2417.25.%20Still%2C%20several%20states%20have%20a%20minimum%20wage%20that%20matches%20the%20federal%20one%2C%20such%20as%20Wisconsin%20and%20Iowa%2C%20and%20places%20like%20Mississippi%20and%20South%20Carolina%20have%20no%20state%20minimum%20wage%2C%20meaning%20%247.25%20is%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20legal%20requirements%2C%20most%20businesses%20are%20now%20paying%20well%20above%20%247.25.%20Part%20of%20this%20is%20thanks%20to%20campaigns%20like%20The%20Fight%20for%20%2415%20%E2%80%94%20as%20in%20a%20%2415%20minimum%20wage%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20for%20years%20been%20a%20progressive%20rallying%20cry%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstimulus-package-pelosi-minimum-wage-increase-coronavirus-relief-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegislative%20push%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(That%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-the-minimum-wage-increase-bernie-sanders-new-bill-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoal%20has%20inched%20up%20to%20%2417%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20proponents%20say%20is%20necessary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-15-minimum-wage-may-worth-when-comes-into-effect-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecause%20of%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20But%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20recent%20increases%20are%20thanks%20to%20the%20super-tight%20post-pandemic%20labor%20market%20in%20which%20companies%20in%20the%20service%20and%20retail%20sectors%20raised%20their%20base%20pay%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20woo%20workers.%20Walmart's%20minimum%20is%20now%20%2414%2C%20and%20it%20says%20its%20average%20associate%20makes%20over%20%2417.50.%20Target's%20starting%20wages%20range%20from%20%2415%20to%20%2424.%20It's%20not%20uncommon%20to%20see%20help-wanted%20signs%20outside%20fast-food%20restaurants%20and%20stores%20advertising%20%2414%20or%20%2415%20an%20hour.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F23%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fminimum-wage.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20has%20pointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20low-wage%20workers%20make%20more%20than%20their%20state's%20minimum%20wage%20basically%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20tricky%20things%20standing%20in%20the%20way%20of%20a%20minimum-wage%20increase%20is%20a%20fear%20of%20what%20mandating%20higher%20pay%20might%20do%20to%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20the%20economy.%20Whenever%20there%20are%20rumblings%20of%20a%20government-ordered%20wage%20hike%2C%20the%20business%20community%20acts%20like%20the%20sky%20is%20falling.%20They%20claim%20that%20higher%20paychecks%20will%20drive%20them%20under%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20the%20little%20guys%20%E2%80%94%20and%20cause%20them%20to%20lay%20off%20workers%20en%20masse.%20Hyperbole%20aside%2C%20it's%20not%20unreasonable%20to%20wonder%20about%20the%20risks%20higher%20wages%20may%20pose.%20For%20workers%2C%20a%20%2415%20wage%20only%20matters%20if%20they%20get%20to%20keep%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20minimum-wage%20increases%20can%20be%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20choose-your-own-adventure%20situation%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20probably%20cherry-pick%20a%20research%20paper%20to%20back%20up%20whatever%20argument%20you're%20making.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fimpacts-of-minimum-wages-review-of-the-international-evidence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20international%20literature%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20minimum%20wages%20found%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20muted%20effect%26quot%3B%20on%20employment%20and%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20the%20earnings%20of%20low-wage%20workers.%20The%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fpublication%2F55681%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneat%20little%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20lets%20you%20play%20around%20with%20its%20estimates%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20a%20federal%20minimum-wage%20hike.%20It%20predicts%20it%20would%20lift%20families%20out%20of%20poverty%20but%20could%20also%20result%20in%20some%20job%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20we%20have%20unemployment%20tick%20up%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20with%20so%20few%20workers%20down%20around%20that%20%247.25%20level%2C%20an%20increase%20is%20not%20going%20to%20affect%20that%20many%20businesses%20significantly%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jacob%20Vigdor%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20impact%20of%20Seattle's%20minimum-wage%20hike%20in%20the%20mid-2010s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVigdor%20said%20his%20research%20found%20a%2099.3%25%20survival%20rate%20for%20Seattle%20businesses%2C%20and%20the%20labor%20market%20when%20the%20move%20was%20enacted%20was%20not%20as%20strong%20as%20it%20is%20now.%20He%20found%20that%20some%20workers%2C%20particularly%20those%20with%20less%20experience%2C%20saw%20their%20hours%20go%20down%20as%20businesses%20tried%20to%20compensate%20but%20that%20most%20people%20still%20saw%20a%20net%20increase%20in%20their%20paychecks.%20He%20said%20teens%20looking%20for%20their%20first%20jobs%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20wound%20up%20being%20losers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore-recent%20hikes%2C%20like%20those%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-fast-food-minimum-wage-newsom-cutting-jobs-losses-employment-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efast-food%20workers%20in%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20don't%20seem%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-minimum-wage-fast-food-qsr-restaurants-silver-lining-candidates-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20tons%20of%20people%20out%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20seeing%20these%20job%20losses%20that%20are%20claimed%20to%20be%20inevitable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Justin%20Wiltshire%2C%20an%20assistant%20economics%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Victoria%20in%20British%20Columbia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firle.berkeley.edu%2Fpublications%2Fworking-papers%2Fminimum-wage-effects-and-monopsony-explanations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20has%20studied%3C%2Fa%3E%20minimum-wage%20hikes%20in%20New%20York%20and%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Reich%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20and%20the%20chair%20of%20UC%20Berkeley's%20Center%20on%20Wage%20and%20Employment%20Dynamics%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20fast-food%20wage%20increases%20in%20New%20York%20and%20California%20were%20absorbed%20by%20small%20price%20increases%2C%20reduced%20turnover%20costs%20(because%20employees%20stayed%20longer)%2C%20and%20reductions%20in%20excess%20profits.%20He%20added%20that%20much%20of%20the%20time%2C%20businesses%20worry%20that%20higher%20prices%20will%20hurt%20their%20sales%20without%20taking%20into%20account%20that%20their%20competitors%20will%20raise%20their%20prices%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20be%20in%20the%20same%20place%2C%20competitively%2C%20that%20they%20were%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20they%20often%20don't%20have%20that%20outlook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Neumark%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20told%20me%20he%20still%20thinks%20a%20higher%20minimum%20would%20lead%20to%20job%20loss.%20He%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20have%20shifted%2C%20but%20he%20still%20doesn't%20think%20the%20federal%20minimum%20ought%20to%20go%20up%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20if%20it%20does%2C%20it%20should%20be%20indexed%20locally%20and%20to%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20certainly%20true%20that%20whatever%20the%20minimum%20wage%20was%20in%20any%20location%20three%20years%20ago%20or%20whatever%2C%20it%20is%20less%20binding%20now%20because%20wages%20have%20gone%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20minimum%20wage%20gets%20so%20high%20that%20it%20starts%20to%20cause%20a%20bunch%20of%20job%20loss%2C%20that's%20a%20problem.%20But%20what%20counts%20as%20%26quot%3Btoo%20high%26quot%3B%20isn't%20easily%20deciphered%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20many%20places%20across%20the%20country%20that%20have%20raised%20the%20minimum%2C%20that%20threshold%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20have%20arrived.%20There%20are%20potential%20trade-offs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20small%20increase%20in%20prices%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20seems%20like%20they%20may%20be%20worth%20it%20in%20the%20name%20of%20putting%20more%20money%20in%20workers'%20pockets%2C%20supporting%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20helping%20businesses%20keep%20their%20staffers%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20impossible%20to%20predict%20the%20exact%20impact%20of%20a%20higher%20minimum%20wage%20at%20the%20federal%20level.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20effect%20would%20depend%20on%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20competition%2C%20geography%2C%20and%2C%20importantly%2C%20the%20amount.%20The%20new%20progressive%20benchmark%20is%20%2417%20an%20hour%2C%20but%20there's%20plenty%20of%20space%20between%20%247.25%20and%20that.%20Some%20of%20the%20aversion%20comes%20down%20to%20a%20simple%20fear%20of%20the%20unknown.%20If%20a%20higher%20minimum%20wage%20lifts%20millions%20of%20people%20out%20of%20poverty%2C%20that's%20incredible.%20But%20you%20also%20can't%20blame%20some%20people%20for%20worrying%20they%20might%20be%20one%20of%20the%20unlucky%20ones%20who%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20finding%20a%20new%20gig%20because%20businesses%20aren't%20hiring%20as%20much.%20You%20also%20can't%20blame%20consumers%20who%20fret%20about%20prices%20creeping%20up%2C%20even%20if%20only%20by%20a%20few%20cents.%20The%20business%20community%20has%20done%20a%20good%20job%20of%20messaging%20that%20higher%20pay%20will%20be%20the%20end%20of%20days%20in%20a%20way%20that%20really%20does%20scare%20people.%20But%20plenty%20of%20businesses%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20their%20workers%20more%2C%20even%20if%20that%20means%20they%20profit%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-minimum-wage-too-low-every-us-county-inflation-mortgage-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20to%20argue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%247.25%20an%20hour%20is%20a%20livable%20wage%20basically%20anywhere%20in%20America.%20That%20amounts%20to%20about%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%20one-third%20of%20the%20median%20wage%20in%20the%20country%2C%20at%20the%20poverty%20line%20for%20individuals%2C%20and%20well%20below%20it%20for%20families.%20In%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20countries%20in%20the%20world%2C%20you%20shouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20work%20a%20full-time%20job%20and%20still%20live%20in%20poverty.%20It's%20good%20for%20everyone%20when%20low-wage%20workers%20have%20more%20money%20in%20their%20bank%20accounts.%20They%20spend%20it%2C%20which%20is%20a%20positive%20for%20the%20economy.%20And%20workers%20at%20the%20very%20bottom%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20helped%20by%20a%20higher%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20look%20at%20several%20of%20the%20states%20that%20do%20not%20have%20minimum%20wage%20above%20%247.25%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20the%20average%20earnings%20of%20low-wage%20workers%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20lot%20lower%20than%20it%20is%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Wiltshire%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20more%20income%20inequality%20between%20the%20median%20worker%20and%20the%20lowest-paid%20worker.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20we've%20seen%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20can%20sustain%20higher%20wages.%20At%20some%20point%20a%20downturn%20will%20hit%2C%20and%20the%20labor%20market%20will%20be%20more%20precarious.%20When%20that%20happens%2C%20workers%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20give%20back%20the%20hard-fought%20gains%20they've%20made%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20given%20the%20evidence%20that%20it's%20not%20necessary.%20Few%20people%20have%20been%20making%20%247.25%20for%20a%20while%20now.%20Businesses%20have%20survived%2C%20as%20has%20the%20economy.%20There's%20no%20good%20reason%20not%20to%20lock%20these%20wins%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-federal-minimum-wage-raise-small-business-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723111023000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3d8f05da406397bf4056d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-federal-minimum-wage-raise-small-business-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Raising%20the%20minimum%20wage%20could%20be%20a%20win-win-win%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20workers%2C%20and%20even%20businesses.%20So%20what's%20stopping%20Washington%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-federal-minimum-wage-raise-small-business-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20couple%20left%20Florida%20to%20live%20on%20a%20sailboat%20exploring%20Europe.%20They%20said%20living%20on%20the%20French%20Riviera%20is%20cheaper%20than%20the%20US.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Doug's%20boat%20in%20Port%20Grimaud%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b37671b4912df3ae1990a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDoug%20moved%20from%20Florida%20to%20his%20sailboat%2C%20now%20stationed%20in%20Port%20Grimaud%20on%20the%20French%20Riviera.%3Cp%3EDoug%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDoug%2C%20a%20computer%20consultant%2C%20has%20been%20working%20from%20his%20sail