stead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20of%20why%20we're%20here%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20explore%20all%20these%20unbelievably%20beautiful%20historical%20areas%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20original%20concept%20of%20the%20Caribbean%20or%20South%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20Doug%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Caribbean%20would%20have%20been%20boring%20very%20quickly%2C%20but%20even%20South%20America%20doesn't%20have%20anywhere%20near%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20on%20so%20many%20different%20levels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20traded%20his%20sailboat%20for%20a%20new%2063-foot%20boat%2C%20shipped%20it%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-americans-make-when-moving-to-italy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EItaly%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2430%2C000%2C%20and%20started%20their%20European%20adventures%20in%20Genoa%20in%20July%202021.%20Doug%20kept%20his%20contract%20positions%2C%20which%20he%20completed%20while%20sailing%20the%20Mediterranean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20thought%20we%20were%20retiring%2C%20but%20I%20got%20a%20call%20from%20a%20headhunter%20and%20got%20an%20offer%20I%20couldn't%20refuse%2C%20so%20I%20started%20doing%20a%20contract%20while%20we%20were%20still%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20it%20carried%20forward%20as%20we%20moved%20to%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20Doug%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb9d86f0-4b94-4ef5-8fa4-0981eb69b3f3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETraveling%20across%20Europe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20few%20months%2C%20Doug%20was%20the%20sole%20income%20source%20before%20his%20wife%20found%20more%20work.%20He%20said%20that%20they%20were%20saving%20more%20money%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20US%2C%20even%20while%20eating%20out%20most%20nights%20and%20staying%20in%20hotels%20in%20upscale%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20first%20summer%2C%20they%20sailed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-do-in-dubrovnik-croatia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDubrovnik%2C%20Croatia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20major%20stops%20in%20Elba%2C%20Corsica%2C%20Sardinia%2C%20Sicily%2C%20and%20Bari.%20At%20each%20stop%2C%20they%20stayed%20at%20the%20port%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20exploring%20each%20destination%20in%20between%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20in%20October%202021%2C%20they%20stayed%20at%20a%20marina%20in%20Dubrovnik%20for%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year%20and%20shipped%20their%20vintage%20car%20from%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20to%20Croatia%20for%20%245%2C000.%20Though%20Americans%20are%20typically%20only%20allowed%20on%20a%20short-stay%20visa%20for%2090%20days%2C%20they%20stayed%20for%20a%20year%20through%20Croatia's%20digital%20nomad%20residence%20permit%20after%20proving%20they%20had%20remote%20jobs%20and%20enough%20money%20to%20be%20self-sustaining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20noticed%20our%20bank%20account%20rising%20faster%20than%20it%20had%20been%20in%20the%20US%20from%20the%20same%20income%2C%20so%20prices%20were%20clearly%20lower%20even%20though%20we%20were%20traveling%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20Doug%20said%2C%20noting%20they%20took%20planes%20to%20cities%20such%20as%20London%20and%20Istanbul%20and%20drove%20to%20Vienna%20and%20Budapest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202022%2C%20they%20moved%20to%20Port%20Montenegro%2C%20a%20marina%20in%20the%20Montenegrin%20town%20of%20Tivat%20about%2050%20miles%20south%20of%20Dubrovnik.%20While%20in%20Montenegro%2C%20they%20flew%20to%20Cairo%20and%20visited%20Athens.%20Doug%20said%20flights%20are%20at%20most%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20round-trip%2C%20with%20some%20totaling%20under%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c2384d7-d5dd-4f35-af35-c028bb115f39%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESettling%20on%20the%20French%20Riviera%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20April%2C%20they%20sailed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-in-france-ways-life-has-been-better-changes-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stopping%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20Malta%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20and%20Malta.%20Six%20months%20later%2C%20they%20settled%20in%20Port%20Grimaud%20on%20the%20French%20Riviera%2C%20paying%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20marina%20costs%20as%20their%20%26quot%3Brent.%26quot%3B%20They%20secured%20long-stay%20visas%2C%20which%20can%20be%20renewed%20every%20year%20until%20they%20become%20permanent%20in%20the%20fifth%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20each%20pay%20%242%2C000%20a%20year%20for%20traveling%20insurance%2C%20though%20they're%20considering%20getting%20French%20tax%20ID%20numbers%20to%20enroll%20in%20the%20free%20healthcare%20system%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20said%20is%20%26quot%3Bunbelievably%20better%20than%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%20Doug's%20wife%20had%20an%20appointment%20with%20a%20cardiologist%2C%20including%20an%20EKG%20and%20cardiac%20sonogram%2C%20for%2095%20euros%20without%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPort%20Grimaud%20is%20located%20just%20west%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-tipping-tourist-europe-france-vacation-blacklist-st-tropez-mayor-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESaint-Tropez%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20he%20said%20this%20area%20is%20less%20touristy%20and%20much%20quieter.%20During%20the%20week%2C%20Doug%20works%20from%20around%203%20p.m.%20to%20midnight%20to%20match%20his%20client's%20schedule%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20Doug%20said%20costs%20have%20been%20lower%20in%20France%20than%20in%20the%20US.%20They%20pay%20much%20less%20for%20marina%20fees%20like%20renting%20a%20boat%20slip%20than%20they%20did%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20boat%20insurance%20is%20about%20equivalent.%20He%20bought%20a%20car%20in%20France%20for%20the%20same%20price%20as%20a%20very%20similar%20car%20in%20the%20US%20but%20with%20twice%20the%20miles%20per%20gallon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20estimates%20food%20prices%20are%20slightly%20lower%20for%20comparable%20restaurants%20or%20grocery%20stores%20in%20the%20US%20but%20often%20far%20higher%20quality%2C%20noting%20the%20food%20is%20often%20fresher%20with%20fewer%20added%20chemicals.%20He%20said%20he's%20gone%20to%20Michelin-star%20restaurants%20in%20France%20for%20under%20100%20euros%20for%20two%20people%2C%20adding%20that%20tipping%20is%20rare.%20He%20said%20wine%20prices%20at%20stores%20and%20restaurants%20in%20France%20are%20sometimes%20three%20to%20four%20times%20cheaper%20than%20what%20he%20paid%20for%20similar%20bottles%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20there%20aren't%20many%20big%20box%20stores%20near%20where%20he%20lives%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20prices%20for%20daily%20expenses%20may%20be%20higher%20for%20some%20items%20because%20the%20quality%20is%20generally%20higher.%20Still%2C%20clothing%20prices%20are%20comparable%20and%20better%20quality%20than%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20he%20got%20a%20custom-made%20jacket%20in%20France%20for%20the%20equivalent%20of%20about%20%24400%2C%20whereas%20a%20lower-quality%20jacket%20at%20Macy's%20would%20be%20%24700.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20hard%20to%20compare%20housing%20prices%2C%20though%20he%20said%20comparably%20sized%20houses%20are%20generally%20cheaper%20in%20France%20and%20are%20built%20much%20sturdier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20added%20that%20education%20is%20typically%20free%20or%20inexpensive%20in%20France%2C%20and%20he's%20noticed%20many%20children%20in%20his%20area%20speak%20three%20or%20four%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20said%20the%20French%20locals%20have%20been%20welcoming%20and%20helpful%2C%20and%20they've%20felt%20safer%20than%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20said%20in%20Florida%2C%20people%20would%20often%20try%20to%20walk%20on%20his%20boat%20or%20take%20photos%20by%20the%20helm%2C%20but%20he's%20felt%20much%20safer%20protecting%20his%20property%20in%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20said%20they%20hope%20to%20retire%20in%20April%202026%20and%20remain%20in%20Europe%2C%20as%20he%20expects%20they%20will%20still%20bring%20in%20about%20%2480%2C000%20a%20year%20from%20retirement%20accounts%20and%20passive%20income.%20Before%20that%2C%20they%20have%20trips%20planned%20to%20Majorca%2C%20Lisbon%2C%20and%20the%20Chinese%20cities%20of%20Beijing%2C%20Shanghai%2C%20and%20Xian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20be%20able%20to%20yacht%20here%2C%20have%20our%20Mercedes%20here%2C%20and%20still%20travel%20all%20that%20we%20feel%20like%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Doug%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20still%20be%20able%20to%20go%20out%20to%20dinner%20whenever%20we%20want%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20have%20to%20follow%20any%20tight%20budget.%20If%20we%20feel%20like%20buying%20an%20extra%20bottle%20of%20wine%20or%20a%20leather%20jacket%2C%20we'll%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20left%20the%20United%20States%20for%20a%20new%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-moved-florida-french-riviera-italy-sailboat-retirement-remote-work-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723111023000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b37695a5247369a3ea2490%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-moved-florida-french-riviera-italy-sailboat-retirement-remote-work-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Doug%2C%20a%20computer%20consultant%2C%20has%20been%20working%20from%20his%20sailboat%20in%20Europe%20for%20three%20years%2C%20recently%20settling%20on%20the%20French%20Riviera%20with%20his%20wife.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-moved-florida-french-riviera-italy-sailboat-retirement-remote-work-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BNo%20Interference%20In%20Any%20Religious%20Body%26quot%3B%3A%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20Defends%20Waqf%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOpposition%20parties%20led%20by%20the%20Congress%20joined%20ranks%20to%20protest%20against%20the%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20today.%20The%20legislation%20aims%20to%20address%20issues%20related%20to%20powers%20of%20State%20Waqf%20Boards%2C%20registration%20and%20survey%20of%20Waqf%20properties%20and%20removal%20of%20encroachment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20proposes%20to%20amend%2044%20sections%20of%20the%201995%20Waqf%20Act.%20The%20Bill%20proposes%20that%20the%20Central%20Waqf%20Council%20and%20state%20Waqf%20Boards%20must%20have%20two%20women.%20It%20also%20lays%20down%20that%20money%20received%20by%20the%20Waqf%20Board%20must%20be%20used%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20widows%2C%20divorcees%2C%20and%20orphans%20in%20the%20manner%20suggested%20by%20the%20government.%20Another%20key%20proposal%20is%20that%20women's%20inheritances%20must%20be%20protected.%20The%20provision%20for%20including%20non-Muslim%20members%20of%20Waqf%20bodies%20is%20another%20contentious%20point%20in%20the%20proposed%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20discussion%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Congress's%20KC%20Venugopal%20termed%20the%20proposed%20law%20%26quot%3Bdraconian%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20is%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20religion%20and%20federal%20system.%20He%20also%20opposed%20the%20provision%20of%20appointing%20non-Muslim%20members%20to%20Waqf%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamajwadi%20Party%2C%20the%20second-largest%20Opposition%20force%2C%20has%20also%20opposed%20the%20Bill.%20%26quot%3BThis%20Bill%20has%20been%20introduced%20as%20part%20of%20well-thought-out%20politics.%20When%20there%20is%20a%20democratic%20process%20for%20election%2C%20why%20nominate%20people.%20No%20person%20from%20outside%20the%20community%20is%20part%20of%20other%20religious%20bodies.%20What%20is%20the%20point%20of%20including%20non-Muslims%20in%20Waqf%20bodies%3F%26quot%3B%20party%20chief%20and%20MP%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5CnAnother%20Samajwadi%20Party%20MP%20Mohibbullah%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20injustice%20to%20Muslims.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20going%20to%20commit%20a%20huge%20mistake%2C%20we%20will%20suffer%20because%20of%20this%20Bill%20for%20centuries.%20This%20is%20interference%20with%20religion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Mr%20Yadav%20had%20alleged%20that%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20sell%20of%20lands%20belonging%20to%20Waqf%20boards%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20amendments.%20%26quot%3BAll%20these%20amendments%20of%20the%20'Waqf%20Board'%20are%20just%20an%20excuse%3B%20Selling%20lands%20like%20defence%2C%20railway%20and%20Nazul%20land%20is%20the%20target%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X.%20While%20Trinamool's%20Sudip%20Bandhyopadhyay%20said%20the%20legislation%20is%20against%20federalism%2C%20DMK's%20K%20Kanimozhi%20said%20it%20is%20against%20the%20minority%20community.%20%26quot%3BWill%20it%20be%20possible%20for%20Christian%20and%20Muslim%20to%20handle%20Hindu%20temples%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDefending%20the%20legislation%2C%20Union%20Minister%20and%20leader%20of%20BJP%20ally%20JDU%2C%20Rajiv%20Ranjan%20Singh%2C%20said%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20brought%20to%20make%20the%20functioning%20of%20Waqf%20boards%20transparent.%20Countering%20the%20Opposition's%20charge%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20against%20minorities%2C%20he%20referred%20to%20the%201984%20anti-Sik%20riots%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20assassination%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20%26quot%3BWho%20killed%20thousands%20of%20Sikhs%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupriya%20Sule%20of%20NCP's%20Shara