22%3Cp%3EThe%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20on%20Thursday%20announced%20its%20Monetary%20Policy%20decision%2C%20keeping%20the%20repo%20rate%20unchanged%20at%206.5%20per%20cent%20for%20the%20ninth%20consecutive%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20was%20made%20by%20the%20Monetary%20Policy%20Committee%20(MPC)%20during%20its%20third%20bi-monthly%20policy%20meeting%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202024-25%2C%20held%20from%20Tuesday%20to%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20Governor%20Shaktikanta%20Das%20cited%20stable%20inflation%20levels%20as%20a%20key%20factor%20in%20the%20decision.%20Retail%20inflation%20rose%20to%205.08%20per%20cent%20year-on-year%20in%20June%20due%20to%20increasing%20food%20prices%20but%20has%20remained%20below%205%20per%20cent%20since%20March%20and%20under%206%20per%20cent%20since%20September%20last%20year.%20The%20CPI-based%20inflation%20has%20been%20within%20the%20RBI's%20tolerance%20range%20of%202-6%20per%20cent%20for%20the%20past%20ten%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20this%20affects%20your%20loan%20EMIs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20breakdown%20of%20how%20this%20decision%20will%20impact%20various%20types%20of%20loans%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHome%20Loans%3A%20The%20interest%20rate%20for%20home%20loans%20linked%20to%20the%20repo%20rate%20will%20stay%20the%20same%2C%20meaning%20EMIs%20for%20existing%20home%20loans%20will%20not%20increase.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAuto%20Loans%3A%20Similar%20to%20home%20loans%2C%20auto%20loans%20linked%20to%20the%20repo%20rate%20will%20not%20see%20a%20change%20in%20their%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPersonal%20Loans%3A%20For%20those%20with%20personal%20loans%20tied%20to%20the%20repo%20rate%2C%20the%20EMIs%20will%2C%20again%2C%20remain%20unchanged.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENew%20Borrowers%3A%20Prospective%20borrowers%20looking%20to%20take%20out%20new%20loans%20can%20expect%20interest%20rates%20to%20remain%20consistent%20with%20the%20current%20levels.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20decision%20ensures%20borrowing%20costs%20do%20not%20rise%2C%20which%20can%20encourage%20spending%20and%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20takeaways%20from%20the%20policy%20meeting%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves%20are%20at%20a%20record%20high%20of%20%24675%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20country's%20external%20sector%20is%20strong.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDomestic%20growth%20is%20steady%2C%20with%20urban%20consumption%20and%20manufacturing%20doing%20well.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EInflation%20is%20expected%20to%20decrease%20gradually.%20The%20RBI%20predicts%20inflation%20will%20be%204.5%20per%20cent%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202024-25.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20RBI%20expects%20India's%20economy%20to%20grow%207.2%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20FY%202024-25.%20Growth%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20steady%20in%20the%20coming%20quarters.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EQuarterly%20GDP%20growth%20projections%20are%20between%207.1%20percent%20and%207.4%20percent.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20CPI%20inflation%20forecast%20for%20FY25%20is%204.5%20percent.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20inflation%20forecast%20for%20Q1FY26%20is%204.4%20percent.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723095360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F0tjadu2g_indian-rupee-generic_625x300_08_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Frepo-rate-unchanged-for-9th-time-what-it-means-for-your-loans-6289792%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Monetary%20Policy%20Committee%20(MPC)%20had%20its%20third%20bi-monthly%20policy%20meeting%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202024-25%20from%20August%206%20to%20August%208.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Frepo-rate-unchanged-for-9th-time-what-it-means-for-your-loans