orn%20on%20the%20head%20to%20show%20beauty%20and%20youthfulness%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Nabam%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20of%20the%20Nyishi%20tribe%20love%20their%20accessories.%20The%20men%20wear%20stone%20bead%20necklaces%2C%20%3Cem%3ETesee%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20while%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20necklaces%20are%20called%20%3Cem%3ESeetir%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Both%20terminate%20at%20the%20waistline%2C%20which%20is%20adorned%20with%20a%20belt%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3ETama%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20worn%20by%20men%2C%20while%20women%20wear%20small%20metal%20discs%20called%20%3Cem%3EHupiya%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20garments%2C%20%3Cem%3ETassh%20Nara%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20black%20cloak%20made%20out%20of%20a%20sago%20palm%20tree%E2%80%99s%20blade-like%20skin%20which%20is%20cut%2C%20dried%2C%20and%20then%20tied%20together%20to%20make%20the%20furry%20coat)%2C%20and%20backpacks%2C%20%3Cem%3ENara%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eare%20festooned%20with%20animal%20fur%20too.%20The%20backpack%20contains%20a%20%3Cem%3Edao%20%3C%2Fem%3E(machete)%2C%20a%20sword%20whose%20cover%20is%20made%20of%20monkey%20skin%2C%20a%20spear%2C%20and%20arrows.%20The%20backpack%20is%20slung%20across%20the%20shoulder%20by%20a%20strap%20made%20of%20bearskin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jewellery%20meanwhile%20includes%20tiger%20nails%2C%20jaws%20of%20the%20tiger%20and%20clouded%20leopard%20%E2%80%94%20both%20%E2%80%98vulnerable%E2%80%99%20according%20to%20the%20IUCN%2C%20and%20teeth%20of%20the%20wild%20boar.%20Nabam%20points%20out%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20Nyishi%20tribe%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F278791%2Fwomen-led-deepa-pawar-anubhuti-uplifts-nomadic-tribes-rights-mental-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20other%20tribes%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20don%20accessories%20made%20out%20of%20animal%20parts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20shares%20that%20the%20parts%20play%20more%20than%20a%20perfunctory%20role.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20jaws%20of%20the%20tiger%20and%20clouded%20leopard%20are%20worn%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3ENyub%20%3C%2Fem%3E(priest)%20and%20%3Cem%3ENyagam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(orator).%20They%20signify%20importance.%20Since%20the%20tiger%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20wearing%20its%20teeth%20indicates%20high%20status%20in%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20teeth%20and%20nails%20of%20tigers%20are%20worn%20to%20enhance%20the%20attire%20and%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20importance.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-1-1722419926-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359177%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20teeth%20and%20nails%20of%20tigers%20are%20worn%20to%20enhance%20the%20attire%20and%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20importance%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Nabam%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20clouded%20leopard%20jaw%20has%20a%20dual%20vantage.%20%E2%80%9COne%20is%20that%20it%20indicates%20the%20person%20is%20important%3B%20it%20is%20also%20believed%20that%20the%20wearer%20gets%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20animal%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nabam%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20anyone%20who%20believes%20that%20tribal%20attire%20is%20incomplete%20without%20animal%20parts%2C%20the%20startup%20has%20a%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Preserve%20culture%20without%20harming%20wildlife%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EOryx%20%E2%80%94%20The%20International%20Journal%20of%20Conservation%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2010)%20by%20Cambridge%20University%20Press%2C%20it%20was%20noted%20that%20out%20of%2033%20mammalian%20species%20hunted%20by%20the%20people%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20at%20the%20time%2C%2020%20were%20%E2%80%98endangered%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98vulnerable%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98near%20threatened%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20IUCN%20Red%20List.%20While%20more%20recent%20statistics%20are%20not%20available%2C%20this%20report%20gives%20a%20picture%20of%20how%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F252451%2Fnanda-kishor-bhujabal-odisha-chilika-lake-mangalajodi-village-poachers-conservator-migratory-birds-sri-sri-mahavir-pakshi-suraksha-samiti-ngo-environment-ecotourism-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunting%20activities%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Northeast%20are%20juxtaposed%20against%20a%20vanishing%20population%20of%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202011%20census%2C%20the%20tribes%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20constitute%2068.78%20percent%20of%20the%20total%20population.%20Their%20numbers%20were%20said%20to%20touch%209%2C51%2C821.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20for%20one%20person%E2%80%99s%20attire%2C%20five%20animals%20are%20killed%2C%20imagine%20how%20many%20animals%20are%20at%20risk%20with%20the%20population%20increasing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nabam%20urges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ft